  27 /* Table for Big5 to UCS conversion.
  28 
  29    With HKSCS mappings 0x8140-0xA0FE and 0xFA40-0xFEFE added; more info:
  30    http://www.ogcio.gov.hk/en/business/tech_promotion/ccli/hkscs/
  31 
  32    Using the charmap:
  33 
  34    sed 's|^%IRREVERSIBLE%||' BIG5-HKSCS |
  35    sed 's|^<U0*\(.....*\)> *.x\(..\)/x\(..\).*|0x\2\3 \1|p;d' |
  36    perl big5.pl
  37 
  38    where big5.pl is:
  39 
  40    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  41    while (<>) {
  42      local($big5, $ucs) = split;
  43      $big5 = hex($big5) - 0x8740;
  44      local($ridx) = int($big5 / 256) * 195 + $big5 % 256;
  45      printf "\n " if (($n % 4) == 0);
  46      ++$n;
  47      printf " [%5d] = 0x%s,", $ridx, $ucs;
  48    }
  49    print "\n";
  50    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  51 */

4672 /* The mapping from Unicode to Big5 is not easy since we have several
4673    separate blocks.
4674 
4675    sed 's|^<U\(....\)>|<U0000\1>|' BIG5-HKSCS |
4676    sort | sed 's|^<U0*\(.....*\)> *./x\(..\)/x\(..\).*|\1 \2\3|p;d' |
4677    perl big5.pl
4678 
4679    where big5.pl is:
4680    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
4681    $first=1;
4682    $old=0x00;
4683    $offset = -1;
4684    sub out {
4685      local($adr, $big5) = @_;
4686      if ($offset % 5 == 0) {
4687        printf ("\n  %s* 0x%04x *%s", "/", $adr, "/");
4688      }
4689      printf (" \"\\x%02x\\x%02x\",", $big5 / 256, $big5  % 256);
4690    }
4691    while (<>) {
4692      local($ucs, $big5) = split;
4693      $big5 = hex($big5);
4694      $ucs = hex($ucs);
4695      if ($ucs - $old >= 128) {
4696        printf "\n";
4697        $first = 0;
4698        $offset=0;
4699      } else {
4700        while ($old + 1 < $ucs) {
4701          out($old, 0);
4702          ++$old;
4703          ++$offset;
4704        }
4705      }
4706      out($ucs, $big5);
4707      $old=$ucs;
4708      ++$offset;
4709    }
4710    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
4711 */

17631    $offset = -1;
17632    while (<>) {
17633      local($ucs, $big5) = split;
17634      $big5 = hex($big5);
17635      $ucs = hex($ucs);
17636      if ($ucs - $old >= 128) {
17637        if ($first != 0) {
17638          printf ("  { 0x%04x, 0x%04x, %5d },\n", $first, $old,
17639                  $offset - ($old - $first));
17640        }
17641        $first = $ucs;
17642      } else {
17643        while ($old + 1 < $ucs) {
17644          ++$old;
17645          ++$offset;
17646        }
17647      }
17648      $old=$ucs;
17649      ++$offset;
17650    }
17651    printf ("  { 0x%04x, 0x%04x, %5d },\n", $first, $old,
17652            $offset - ($old - $first));
17653    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
17654  */

17733 /* Definitions used in the body of the `gconv' function.  */
17734 #define CHARSET_NAME        "BIG5HKSCS//"
17735 #define FROM_LOOP       from_big5hkscs
17736 #define TO_LOOP         to_big5hkscs
17737 #define DEFINE_INIT     1
17738 #define DEFINE_FINI     1
17739 #define ONE_DIRECTION       0
17740 #define FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM   1
17741 #define FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM   2
17742 #define FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO     4
17743 #define FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO     8
17744 #define TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM     4
17745 #define TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM     4
17746 #define TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO       1
17747 #define TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO       2
17748 #define PREPARE_LOOP \
17749   int saved_state;                                \
17750   int *statep = &data->__statep->__count;
17751 #define EXTRA_LOOP_ARGS     , statep
17752 
17753 
17754 /* Since we might have to reset input pointer we must be able to save
17755    and restore the state.  */
17756 #define SAVE_RESET_STATE(Save) \
17757   if (Save)                                   \
17758     saved_state = *statep;                            \
17759   else                                        \
17760     *statep = saved_state
17761 
17762 
17763 /* During BIG5-HKSCS to UCS-4 conversion, the COUNT element of the state
17764    contains the last UCS-4 character, shifted by 3 bits.
17765    During UCS-4 to BIG5-HKSCS conversion, the COUNT element of the state
17766    contains the last two bytes to be output, shifted by 3 bits.  */
17767 
17768 /* Since this is a stateful encoding we have to provide code which resets
17769    the output state to the initial state.  This has to be done during the
17770    flushing.  */
17771 #define EMIT_SHIFT_TO_INIT \
17772   if (data->__statep->__count != 0)                       \
17773     {                                         \
17774       if (FROM_DIRECTION)                             \
17775     {                                     \
17776       if (__glibc_likely (outbuf + 4 <= outend))                  \
17777         {                                     \
17778           /* Write out the last character.  */                \
17779           *((uint32_t *) outbuf) = data->__statep->__count >> 3;          \
17780           outbuf += sizeof (uint32_t);                    \
17781           data->__statep->__count = 0;                    \
17782         }                                     \
17783       else                                    \
17784         /* We don't have enough room in the output buffer.  */        \
17785         status = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
17786     }                                     \
17787       else                                    \
17788     {                                     \
17789       if (__glibc_likely (outbuf + 2 <= outend))                  \
17790         {                                     \
17791           /* Write out the last character.  */                \
17792           uint32_t lasttwo = data->__statep->__count >> 3;            \
17793           *outbuf++ = (lasttwo >> 8) & 0xff;                  \
17794           *outbuf++ = lasttwo & 0xff;                     \
17795           data->__statep->__count = 0;                    \
17796         }                                     \
17797       else                                    \
17798         /* We don't have enough room in the output buffer.  */        \
17799         status = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
17800     }                                     \
17801     }
17802 
17803 
17804 /* First define the conversion function from Big5 to UCS4.  */
17805 #define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT    FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM
17806 #define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT    FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM
17807 #define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT   FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO
17808 #define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT   FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO
17809 #define LOOPFCT         FROM_LOOP
17810 #define BODY \
17811   {                                       \
17812     uint32_t ch;                                  \
17813                                           \
17814     /* Determine whether there is a buffered character pending.  */       \
17815     ch = *statep >> 3;                                \
17816     if (__glibc_likely (ch == 0))                         \
17817       {                                       \
17818     /* No - so look at the next input byte.  */               \
17819     ch = *inptr;                                  \
17820                                           \
17821     if (ch >= 0x81 && ch <= 0xfe)                         \
17822       {                                   \
17823         /* Two-byte character.  First test whether the next byte          \
17824            is also available.  */                         \
17825         uint32_t ch2;                             \
17826         int idx;                                  \
17827                                           \
17828         if (__glibc_unlikely (inptr + 1 >= inend))                \
17829           {                                   \
17830         /* The second character is not available.  */             \
17831         result = __GCONV_INCOMPLETE_INPUT;                \
17832         break;                                \
17833           }                                   \
17834                                           \
17835         ch2 = inptr[1];                           \
17836         idx = (ch - 0x87) * 195 + ch2 - 0x40;                 \
17837         /* See whether the second byte is in the correct range.  */       \
17838         if (ch < 0x87 || ch2 < 0x40 || ch2 > 0xfe                 \
17839         || (ch = big5hkscs_to_ucs[idx]) == 0)                 \
17840           {                                   \
17841         /* Check for special cases: combining characters.  */         \
17842         if (idx == 195 + 0x22 /* 8862 */)                 \
17843           {                               \
17844             ch = 0xca;                            \
17845             ch2 = 0x304;                          \
17846           }                               \
17847         else if (idx == 195 + 0x24 /* 8864 */)                \
17848           {                               \
17849             ch = 0xca;                            \
17850             ch2 = 0x30c;                          \
17851           }                               \
17852         else if (idx == 195 + 0x63 /* 88a3 */)                \
17853           {                               \
17854             ch = 0xea;                            \
17855             ch2 = 0x304;                          \
17856           }                               \
17857         else if (idx == 195 + 0x65 /* 88a5 */)                \
17858           {                               \
17859             ch = 0xea;                            \
17860             ch2 = 0x30c;                          \
17861           }                               \
17862         else                                  \
17863           /* This is illegal.  */                     \
17864           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1);                 \
17865                                           \
17866         inptr += 2;                           \
17867                                           \
17868         put32 (outptr, ch);                       \
17869         outptr += 4;                              \
17870                                           \
17871         /* See whether we have room for two characters.  */       \
17872         if (outptr + 4 <= outend)                     \
17873           {                               \
17874             put32 (outptr, ch2);                      \
17875             outptr += 4;                          \
17876             continue;                             \
17877           }                               \
17878                                           \
17879         /* Otherwise store only the first character now, and          \
17880            put the second one into the queue.  */             \
17881         *statep = ch2 << 3;                       \
17882         /* Tell the caller why we terminate the loop.  */         \
17883         result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
17884         break;                                \
17885           }                                   \
17886                                           \
17887         inptr += 2;                               \
17888       }                                   \
17889     else if (__glibc_unlikely (ch == 0xff))                   \
17890       {                                   \
17891         STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1);                   \
17892       }                                   \
17893     else                                      \
17894       ++inptr;                                \
17895       }                                       \
17896     else                                      \
17897       /* Clear the queue and proceed to output the saved character.  */       \
17898       *statep = 0;                                \
17899                                           \
17900     put32 (outptr, ch);                               \
17901     outptr += 4;                                  \
17902   }
17903 #define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
17904 #define EXTRA_LOOP_DECLS    , int *statep
17905 #define ONEBYTE_BODY \
17906   {                                       \
17907     if (c <= 0x80)                                \
17908       return c;                                   \
17909     else                                      \
17910       return WEOF;                                \
17911   }
17912 #include <iconv/loop.c>
17913 
17914 
17915 /* Next, define the other direction.  */
17916 #define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT    TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM
17917 #define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT    TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM
17918 #define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT   TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO
17919 #define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT   TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO
17920 #define LOOPFCT         TO_LOOP
17921 #define BODY \
17922   {                                       \
17923     uint32_t ch = get32 (inptr);                          \
17924                                           \
17925     if ((*statep >> 3) != 0)                              \
17926       {                                       \
17927     /* Attempt to combine the last character with this one.  */       \
17928     uint16_t lasttwo = *statep >> 3;                      \
17929                                           \
17930     if (ch == 0x304 && lasttwo == 0x8866)                     \
17931       ch = 0x8862;                                \
17932     else if (ch == 0x30c && lasttwo == 0x8866)                \
17933       ch = 0x8864;                                \
17934     else if (ch == 0x304 && lasttwo == 0x88a7)                \
17935       ch = 0x88a3;                                \
17936     else if (ch == 0x30c && lasttwo == 0x88a7)                \
17937       ch = 0x88a5;                                \
17938     else                                      \
17939       goto not_combining;                             \
17940                                           \
17941     /* Output the combined character.  */                     \
17942     if (__glibc_unlikely (outptr + 1 >= outend))                  \
17943       {                                   \
17944         result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
17945         break;                                \
17946       }                                   \
17947     *outptr++ = (ch >> 8) & 0xff;                         \
17948     *outptr++ = ch & 0xff;                            \
17949     *statep = 0;                                  \
17950     inptr += 4;                               \
17951     continue;                                 \
17952                                           \
17953       not_combining:                                  \
17954     /* Output the buffered character.  */                     \
17955     if (__glibc_unlikely (outptr + 1 >= outend))                  \
17956       {                                   \
17957         result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
17958         break;                                \
17959       }                                   \
17960     *outptr++ = (lasttwo >> 8) & 0xff;                    \
17961     *outptr++ = lasttwo & 0xff;                       \
17962     *statep = 0;                                  \
17963     continue;                                 \
17964       }                                       \
17965                                           \
17966     if (ch <= 0x0080)                                 \
17967       *outptr++ = ch;                                 \
17968     else                                      \
17969       {                                       \
17970     const unsigned char *cp = (const unsigned char *) "";             \
17971     size_t i;                                 \
17972                                               \
17973     for (i = 0;                               \
17974          i < sizeof (from_ucs4_idx) / sizeof (from_ucs4_idx[0]);          \
17975          ++i)                                 \
17976       {                                   \
17977         if (ch < from_ucs4_idx[i].from)                   \
17978           break;                                  \
17979         if (from_ucs4_idx[i].to >= ch)                    \
17980           {                                   \
17981         cp = from_ucs4[from_ucs4_idx[i].offset                \
17982                    + ch - from_ucs4_idx[i].from];             \
17983         break;                                \
17984           }                                   \
17985       }                                   \
17986                                           \
17987     if (cp[0] == '\0')                            \
17988       {                                   \
17989         UNICODE_TAG_HANDLER (ch, 4);                      \
17990                                           \
17991         /* Illegal character.  */                         \
17992         STANDARD_TO_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (4);                     \
17993       }                                   \
17994     else                                      \
17995       {                                   \
17996        /* Check for possible combining character.  */             \
17997         if (__glibc_unlikely (ch == 0xca || ch == 0xea))              \
17998           {                                   \
17999         *statep = ((cp[0] << 8) | cp[1]) << 3;                \
18000         inptr += 4;                           \
18001         continue;                             \
18002           }                                   \
18003                                           \
18004         /* See whether there is enough room to write the second byte.  */ \
18005         if (__builtin_expect (cp[1] != '\0', 1)               \
18006         && __builtin_expect (outptr + 1 >= outend, 0))            \
18007           {                                   \
18008         /* We have not enough room.  */                   \
18009         result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
18010         break;                                \
18011           }                                   \
18012                                           \
18013         *outptr++ = cp[0];                            \
18014         if (__glibc_likely (cp[1] != '\0'))                   \
18015           *outptr++ = cp[1];                          \
18016       }                                   \
18017       }                                       \
18018                                           \
18019     inptr += 4;                                   \
18020   }
18021 #define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
18022 #define EXTRA_LOOP_DECLS    , int *statep
18023 #include <iconv/loop.c>
